### Read cookies in Next.js Server Components (TypeScript/JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

This example demonstrates how to use the `cookies` function from `next/headers` to asynchronously retrieve an incoming HTTP cookie value within a Server Component. It imports the `cookies` function, awaits its result to get a `cookieStore` object, and then uses `get('theme')` to read a specific cookie.

```tsx
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export default async function Page() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  const theme = cookieStore.get('theme')
  return '...'
}
```

