### Read, set, and delete cookies in Next.js API routes using `next/headers`

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/route.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to read, set, and delete cookies within Next.js API routes using the `cookies` function from `next/headers`. It shows direct interaction with the cookie store for common operations.

```ts
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()

  const a = cookieStore.get('a')
  const b = cookieStore.set('b', '1')
  const c = cookieStore.delete('c')
}
```

