### Check for Cookie Existence in Next.js with `cookies().has()` (TS/JSX)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

This example illustrates how to check for the presence of a specific cookie using the `cookies().has(name)` method in Next.js Server Components. It first retrieves the cookie store and then efficiently checks if a cookie with the given name, such as 'theme', currently exists.

```tsx
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

