### Set HTTP Cookies in Next.js Server Components (TS/JS)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to set a cookie using the `cookies().set()` method in Next.js Server Actions or Route Handlers. It shows examples with basic name-value pairs, setting the secure flag, and utilizing a full options object including `httpOnly` and `path` for advanced configuration.

```tsx
'use server'

import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function create(data) {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()

  cookieStore.set('name', 'lee')
  // or
  cookieStore.set('name', 'lee', { secure: true })
  // or
  cookieStore.set({
    name: 'name',
    value: 'lee',
    httpOnly: true,
    path: '/',
  })
}
```

